1
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,667
What will you do first
when we get back to Manila?

2
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:20,833
I will hug my parents.

3
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:22,867
I will hug my mom too.

4
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:26,000
And I will kiss her many times.

5
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:28,133
Wherever my daughter is,

6
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:32,100
I hope someone will give
her food to eat.

7
00:00:32,167 --> 00:00:33,200
Yen, there are rocks!

8
00:00:33,267 --> 00:00:34,100
Hold on tight!

9
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,400
Tie yourself up!

10
00:00:35,467 --> 00:00:37,100
We're gonna hit the rocks!

11
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:38,267
Hold on tight!

12
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:40,767
Yen!

13
00:00:43,367 --> 00:00:43,900
Hello?

14
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:45,000
Sir Victor,

15
00:00:45,067 --> 00:00:47,600
they recovered remains
from the plane crash.

16
00:00:47,667 --> 00:00:49,633
They were from
your son's school.

17
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:50,600
Is it Red?

18
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:52,600
I feel that Yenyen
is still alive.

19
00:00:52,667 --> 00:00:55,533
But I'm scared to
check on the bodies.

20
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,900
What if one of
them is Yenyen?

21
00:00:57,967 --> 00:00:59,733
I don't want to
prolong our agony!

22
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:04,467
I want to know if our
son is dead or not.

23
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:06,133
She's not my daughter.

24
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:07,333
She's not her.

25
00:01:07,433 --> 00:01:08,567
Thank you.

26
00:01:11,367 --> 00:01:13,067
He's not my son.

27
00:01:13,133 --> 00:01:13,967
Oh, wow.

28
00:01:14,033 --> 00:01:15,067
You're also here.

29
00:01:15,133 --> 00:01:17,367
So, do you want me to
order you a coffin?

30
00:01:17,433 --> 00:01:18,633
My daughter's not dead.

31
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:19,633
Too bad.

32
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:21,367
I wish it was your
daughter who died.

33
00:01:21,433 --> 00:01:24,633
Your horns and
tail are growing.

34
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,200
You're turning
into a demon!

35
00:01:26,267 --> 00:01:28,267
You're such a witch!

36
00:01:30,433 --> 00:01:32,967
My boyfriend is
also dear to me.

37
00:01:33,033 --> 00:01:37,033
So I got so sad too
when we got separated.

38
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:38,667
I miss Red.

39
00:01:41,933 --> 00:01:43,133
Red?

40
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:46,100
Red is the name of the man
I was with on the island.

41
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,333
Rina, are you done?

42
00:02:03,367 --> 00:02:05,533
Look who I found here.

43
00:02:06,533 --> 00:02:08,333
Why is she lying there?

44
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:11,200
Stop asking questions.

45
00:02:11,267 --> 00:02:13,000
Just help me out here.

46
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:17,067
I have a brilliant idea.

47
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:18,433
What are you planning to do?

48
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:23,500
Let's put her in a body bag.

49
00:02:23,567 --> 00:02:25,467
Are you serious?

50
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:28,067
Hurry up before
someone sees us.

51
00:02:28,133 --> 00:02:29,233
Come on.

52
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,333
Come on.

53
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:37,667
Do you know Red?

54
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:41,500
He's a very nice guy.

55
00:02:42,767 --> 00:02:44,333
You know what,

56
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:47,033
he took care of me.

57
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:51,067
And when he was sick,
I took care of him.

58
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:55,033
He gave me a lot
of fruits to eat.

59
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:59,000
And this bracelet,
he gave this to me.

60
00:02:59,067 --> 00:03:03,867
So we'll always
think of each other.

61
00:03:05,867 --> 00:03:07,500
I miss Red.

62
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:11,933
I hope he's doing well.

63
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,567
I hope he's safe.

64
00:03:18,067 --> 00:03:21,200
I hope we see each other.

65
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:23,267
I miss Red too.

66
00:03:26,233 --> 00:03:28,433
You know Red?

67
00:03:32,767 --> 00:03:34,867
So what are you trying to say?

68
00:03:36,267 --> 00:03:38,200
Are you breaking up with me?

69
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:43,267
Sab, we can still be friends.

70
00:03:45,233 --> 00:03:46,500
Are you serious?

71
00:03:46,567 --> 00:03:48,033
Red, no!

72
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,833
I don't want to
break up with you.

73
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:52,533
Red, I love you so much!

74
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,767
Please don't do this!

75
00:03:54,867 --> 00:03:57,867
Why? Did I do something wrong?

76
00:03:57,933 --> 00:03:59,133
Is it my fault?

77
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,833
No.

78
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:02,533
We're always fighting.

79
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:05,900
Our relationship
became too toxic.

80
00:04:05,967 --> 00:04:08,233
You like the things
I don't like.

81
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:10,400
And I like the things
that you don't.

82
00:04:10,467 --> 00:04:12,833
How can we be happy with that?

83
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,967
Is that all?

84
00:04:15,033 --> 00:04:16,333
I'll change.

85
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,567
I'll do everything.

86
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:19,967
I'll change,
to make you happy again.

87
00:04:20,033 --> 00:04:20,833
Just don't do this.

88
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:22,567
- Don't leave me, please.
- Sab.

89
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:24,300
- Please.
- Babe, don't do this!

90
00:04:24,367 --> 00:04:26,933
Please, don't
cry like that.

91
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,867
We've tried so many times.

92
00:04:33,233 --> 00:04:35,700
But it didn't work.

93
00:04:35,767 --> 00:04:39,667
Maybe we're really not
meant for each other.

94
00:04:39,733 --> 00:04:41,833
But it's you that I want.

95
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:45,367
Red, please.

96
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,367
I'm sorry, Sab.

97
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:57,633
Just tell me.

98
00:04:57,700 --> 00:04:58,667
Tell me now.

99
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,533
Is there a third party?

100
00:05:04,167 --> 00:05:05,867
Do you have someone else
that's why you're doing this?

101
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:06,433
No.

102
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,767
No, no.

103
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:09,067
No, Sab.

104
00:05:09,133 --> 00:05:11,233
There's no one else.

105
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:13,667
Why are you accusing
me of these things?

106
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:17,567
Sab, it's just that I just
want to get out of this

107
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:18,867
unhealthy relationship.

108
00:05:18,933 --> 00:05:20,833
It's too toxic for me.

109
00:05:25,267 --> 00:05:28,633
Sab, don't think that
I never loved you.

110
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:31,633
Because I loved you.

111
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:33,600
Okay?

112
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,267
Please,

113
00:05:36,367 --> 00:05:38,667
I hope you can
accept my decision.

114
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:42,400
I hope you understand.

115
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:45,200
You can't do this to me.

116
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:50,133
Sab, it's over.

117
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,533
You can't do this to me.

118
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,133
- Red.
- Sorry.

119
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,933
You can't leave me like this.

120
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,467
Red, you can't do this to me.

121
00:05:56,533 --> 00:05:57,567
Red!

122
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:59,433
Red, how could
you do this to me?

123
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:02,533
You're mine!

124
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,700
You think it's that easy?

125
00:06:04,767 --> 00:06:06,233
No!

126
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:07,533
No, you're mine.

127
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:10,500
You're mine, Red.
You can't do this to me.

128
00:06:10,567 --> 00:06:11,900
You can't.

129
00:06:11,967 --> 00:06:14,067
You can't do this to me.

130
00:06:15,367 --> 00:06:17,067
You're mine.

131
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,233
Yes.

132
00:06:21,067 --> 00:06:22,800
I know Red so well.

133
00:06:28,233 --> 00:06:29,333
Yen!

134
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,700
Put your hands in the air!

135
00:06:32,567 --> 00:06:33,467
Who are you?

136
00:06:33,533 --> 00:06:35,267
How did you know Yenyen?

137
00:06:47,267 --> 00:06:49,133
I was with Yen.

138
00:06:50,167 --> 00:06:51,567
I'm not a bad person.

139
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:04,700
OMG!

140
00:07:04,767 --> 00:07:05,700
Red?

141
00:07:05,767 --> 00:07:06,833
Is that you?

142
00:07:08,133 --> 00:07:09,400
You know me?

143
00:07:09,467 --> 00:07:10,433
Of course!

144
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,700
You're the most good-looking
soccer player!

145
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,533
I am Yenyen's BFF!

146
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:22,267
Everyone knows Red, right?

147
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:23,700
He's super famous.

148
00:07:23,767 --> 00:07:24,800
Yes.

149
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:28,067
He's one of the...

150
00:07:28,133 --> 00:07:30,500
star soccer players on campus.

151
00:07:30,567 --> 00:07:33,600
- Yes, that's him.
 - I know, right?

152
00:07:33,667 --> 00:07:35,067
And...

153
00:07:36,267 --> 00:07:39,667
a lot of girls like her.

154
00:07:39,733 --> 00:07:40,933
Right.

155
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,300
He's good-looking
and a rich kid.

156
00:07:46,767 --> 00:07:49,567
When did you last see him?

157
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:58,200
We got separated in the sea
when the raft collapsed.

158
00:07:58,267 --> 00:08:02,033
But I feel that he's
around here too.

159
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:04,200
Why don't we look for him?

160
00:08:06,633 --> 00:08:07,700
Are you okay?

161
00:08:07,767 --> 00:08:08,833
Sit down first.

162
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:10,133
Sit down.

163
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,200
I'll go look for Red, okay?

164
00:08:12,267 --> 00:08:14,567
I will tell him
that you're here.

165
00:08:14,633 --> 00:08:17,433
Here, eat first.

166
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:19,867
Thank you, Sabina.

167
00:08:19,933 --> 00:08:21,600
I can't imagine
what could happen to me

168
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:23,900
if I got to the other island.

169
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:26,833
I'm also grateful
that you're here with me.

170
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:28,633
So eat first.

171
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:29,633
Regain your strength.

172
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:31,433
And get some rest.

173
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:33,567
I'll go look for Red.

174
00:09:10,933 --> 00:09:11,933
Help!

175
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:19,367
Help!

176
00:09:24,233 --> 00:09:25,400
Help!

177
00:09:43,367 --> 00:09:44,900
Oh my god!

178
00:09:44,967 --> 00:09:46,567
I can't breathe.

179
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,133
Help!

180
00:09:54,433 --> 00:09:55,700
Help!

181
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:01,700
Really?

182
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,100
I can't believe
coach is already gone.

183
00:10:04,167 --> 00:10:06,233
I didn't get to hug her.

184
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:08,900
Yeah.

185
00:10:08,967 --> 00:10:11,800
Even Yenyen was devastated.

186
00:10:11,867 --> 00:10:14,000
I'm glad you two were together.

187
00:10:14,067 --> 00:10:15,667
How's my best friend?

188
00:10:16,633 --> 00:10:18,300
Well, she's okay.

189
00:10:18,367 --> 00:10:19,833
But...

190
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:21,767
we got separated.

191
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:26,300
Since you're here,

192
00:10:26,367 --> 00:10:28,933
she may be here too.

193
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:33,367
Can you help me find her?

194
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:34,167
Yes!

195
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:36,133
Of course!

196
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:38,933
I somehow know my way
around this island.

197
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,200
Let's do this.

198
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:41,700
We should split.

199
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:43,700
So we can find her faster.

200
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:46,600
And before the sun sets,

201
00:10:46,667 --> 00:10:48,000
we should meet here again.

202
00:10:48,067 --> 00:10:49,067
Okay?

203
00:10:50,633 --> 00:10:51,867
Okay.

204
00:10:51,933 --> 00:10:53,033
I'm okay with it.

205
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:57,433
I'll search the whole
island just to find her.

206
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:59,533
I can't lose her.

207
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:01,600
Yen!

208
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:08,533
Why do I feel that there's
something else to what he said?

209
00:11:08,633 --> 00:11:10,533
I feel something's going on.

210
00:11:14,467 --> 00:11:15,467
Yen!

211
00:11:21,367 --> 00:11:21,967
Here.

212
00:11:22,033 --> 00:11:23,067
I have clothes here.

213
00:11:23,133 --> 00:11:26,267
You should change.
Your clothing is still wet.

214
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:27,567
Thank you.

215
00:11:29,233 --> 00:11:33,533
I don't know what can happen
to me if I am on another island.

216
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,600
We only have each other.

217
00:11:35,667 --> 00:11:37,033
We need to survive.

218
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:40,300
I'm thinking about Red.

219
00:11:42,700 --> 00:11:44,933
I hope he gets to eat.

220
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,400
I hope he's safe.

221
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,233
Don't worry.

222
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:51,933
I'll look for him, okay?

223
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,933
I'll search the island for him.

224
00:11:56,667 --> 00:11:58,567
I'll go with you.

225
00:11:58,633 --> 00:11:59,567
What?

226
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:01,633
No, no. Just stay here.

227
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:04,133
I'll come back once I find Red.

228
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,300
Thank you, Sabina.

229
00:12:07,367 --> 00:12:11,333
I don't know how I can
repay your kindness.

230
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,500
No worries.

231
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,400
Okay. Just stay here.

232
00:12:16,467 --> 00:12:17,533
Get some rest.

233
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,767
I'll look for him.

234
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:20,700
Don't leave, okay?

235
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,900
Dindi!

236
00:13:13,967 --> 00:13:16,233
Zandro, you better go home.

237
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:17,167
Get out of here.

238
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:18,933
I've already talked
to Victor anyway.

239
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,867
He's on his way here.

240
00:13:19,933 --> 00:13:21,433
I'll just wait for him.

241
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:22,467
Wait, Rina.

242
00:13:22,533 --> 00:13:24,700
Are we going to leave
Amanda like that?

243
00:13:27,867 --> 00:13:29,267
Is Amanda here?

244
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:31,733
What do you mean
by what you said?

245
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,433
What is it, Zandro?

246
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,400
Nothing, Victor.

247
00:13:37,467 --> 00:13:39,000
Go ahead, Zandro.

248
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:43,500
You're not leaving until
you answer my question.

249
00:13:43,567 --> 00:13:45,533
Did you do something to Amanda?

250
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,900
Do I need to repeat my question?

251
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:54,500
Amanda and I fought, okay?

252
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:57,733
She fainted, so we left her
there.

253
00:13:59,633 --> 00:14:01,700
You left her unconscious?

254
00:14:01,767 --> 00:14:02,700
Where?

255
00:14:06,067 --> 00:14:07,200
She's in the morgue.

256
00:14:07,267 --> 00:14:09,300
Are you out of your mind?

257
00:14:09,367 --> 00:14:11,400
She can get back at us!

258
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:12,800
She can sue you.

259
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:15,733
Then I'll see her in court.

260
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,800
I won't back down!

261
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:37,100
Hello, Dindi.

262
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:39,400
Hello, Amanda?

263
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:40,333
Dindi!

264
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:42,100
Why?

265
00:14:42,567 --> 00:14:44,267
I can't...

266
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:49,033
I can't breathe.

267
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:51,067
Help me.

268
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:54,467
They put me inside a...

269
00:14:54,533 --> 00:14:55,533
body bag.

270
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,533
I can't breathe.

271
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:03,100
Help!

272
00:15:03,167 --> 00:15:04,367
Dindi!

273
00:15:05,967 --> 00:15:07,533
Hello, Dindi!

274
00:15:10,633 --> 00:15:12,000
Dindi!

275
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:17,300
Hello, Dindi!

276
00:15:19,633 --> 00:15:21,233
Help!

277
00:15:52,733 --> 00:15:54,100
I'll change.

278
00:15:54,167 --> 00:15:55,367
I'll do everything.

279
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:57,667
I'll change,
to make you happy again.

280
00:15:57,733 --> 00:15:58,533
Just don't do this.

281
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,333
- Don't leave me, please.
- Sab.

282
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,100
- Please.
- Babe, don't do this!

283
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:04,667
Please, don't cry like that.

284
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:10,933
We've already tried
so many times.

285
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:13,433
But it didn't work.

286
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:17,433
Maybe we're not
meant for each other.

287
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:20,267
But it's you that I want.

288
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:47,600
Sabina!

289
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:52,367
Sabina!

290
00:16:55,667 --> 00:16:57,100
Sabina!

291
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:03,300
I need to do something.

292
00:17:03,367 --> 00:17:05,300
I need to look for Red.

293
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:07,767
I hope nothing bad
happened to him.

294
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:16,167
Sabina!

295
00:17:32,633 --> 00:17:33,467
Red?

296
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,433
Red!

297
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:37,567
Sab?

298
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,900
Red?

299
00:17:39,967 --> 00:17:41,200
- Oh my god!
- Sab!

300
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:42,400
Oh my god!
Is that really you?

301
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,800
You're alive!

302
00:17:44,867 --> 00:17:46,700
I've looked for you
for a long time!

303
00:17:46,767 --> 00:17:47,500
Are you okay?

304
00:17:47,567 --> 00:17:48,567
Are you hurt?

305
00:17:48,667 --> 00:17:50,767
Oh my god!

306
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:51,500
Oh, so good!
Sab.

307
00:17:52,567 --> 00:17:54,967
It feels so good to hug you.

308
00:17:55,033 --> 00:17:56,533
Sab, I'm okay.

309
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,633
I'm so happy to see you too.

310
00:18:00,933 --> 00:18:04,467
I'm sorry if we didn't
end things on a good note.

311
00:18:04,533 --> 00:18:06,333
Don't think about that.

312
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:09,300
What matters is we're together.

313
00:18:09,367 --> 00:18:10,767
And we're alive.

314
00:18:14,433 --> 00:18:16,867
I'm looking for a woman.

315
00:18:16,933 --> 00:18:18,900
We got separated
from the other island.

316
00:18:18,967 --> 00:18:20,533
Did you see her?

317
00:18:23,567 --> 00:18:24,333
Wait...
Sab?

318
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:27,200
- Sab!
- Sorry.
- I'm feeling dizzy.
- Sab, are you okay?

319
00:18:28,133 --> 00:18:29,067
Sit down first.

320
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:30,200
Get some rest.

321
00:18:37,667 --> 00:18:38,867
Sabina!

322
00:18:40,367 --> 00:18:41,600
Rest here for now.

323
00:18:41,667 --> 00:18:43,333
I'm just gonna look around.

324
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:43,833
Where are you going?
Wait.

325
00:18:44,533 --> 00:18:46,067
Don't leave.

326
00:18:46,133 --> 00:18:47,233
Don't leave me, please.

327
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:49,800
I'm having a hard time.

328
00:18:51,867 --> 00:18:54,600
I was all alone here.

329
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,633
I was...

330
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:58,000
I was lucky enough
to find some supplies,

331
00:18:58,067 --> 00:19:00,767
but it didn't last long.

332
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:04,367
I haven't eaten for days.

333
00:19:04,433 --> 00:19:07,067
I was alone here,
and I was so scared.

334
00:19:07,133 --> 00:19:11,100
So can you please just
stay here for a while?

335
00:19:14,967 --> 00:19:17,467
Sab, I'm right here.

336
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:25,033
I'll go look for
something to eat.

337
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:26,167
So you can eat.

338
00:19:26,233 --> 00:19:27,167
Wait here.

339
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:29,633
Be safe.

340
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:42,567
Sabina!

341
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,167
Sabina!

342
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:54,900
Sabina, are you here?

343
00:19:58,533 --> 00:19:59,533
Sabina.

344
00:20:02,867 --> 00:20:04,067
Sabina!

345
00:20:08,233 --> 00:20:10,367
Sabina, are you here?

346
00:20:12,867 --> 00:20:13,933
Sabina!

347
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:34,900
Sab.
Red, let's go.

348
00:20:35,967 --> 00:20:36,967
- Eat first.
- Let's go somewhere else.

349
00:20:37,033 --> 00:20:37,967
- What?
- Let's get out of here.

350
00:20:38,033 --> 00:20:40,433
There might be
wild animals here.

351
00:20:41,867 --> 00:20:42,833
What? Wild animals?

352
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:44,300
Yes.

353
00:20:44,367 --> 00:20:45,100
Come on.

354
00:20:45,167 --> 00:20:46,133
- Let's go now.
- Wait.

355
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,100
Eat first.

356
00:20:47,167 --> 00:20:48,267
Eat first, okay?

357
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:50,400
So won't get dizzy
when you walk.

358
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:52,867
Wait.

359
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:58,533
I found a lot of
fruits over there.

360
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:01,000
Why did you get yourself hungry?

361
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:03,033
And you have a jungle bolo.

362
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:04,333
Why don't you use it?

363
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:07,333
By the way, Sab.

364
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,933
I found this earlier.

365
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,733
Thank God you found it.

366
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:19,133
I thank God that I found you.

367
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:23,567
Sabina!

368
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:27,667
Sabina!

369
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,467
Help!

370
00:21:33,533 --> 00:21:34,333
Amanda!

371
00:21:42,967 --> 00:21:44,967
Thank you so much!

372
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:30,633
Red?

373
00:22:38,133 --> 00:22:39,267
Sabina?

374
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:50,267
You know each other?

375
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:54,500
I'm asking you...

376
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:56,600
as a fellow woman.

377
00:22:56,667 --> 00:23:00,333
Just please stay away
from my boyfriend.

378
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:03,567
Because I just can't
afford to lose him again.

379
00:23:03,633 --> 00:23:09,867
I don't want Eden to worry about
my past when she gets back.

380
00:23:09,933 --> 00:23:13,400
I will make Rina suffer the same
way she makes me suffer.

381
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:15,000
I will sue her, Dindi.

382
00:23:15,067 --> 00:23:16,900
I don't want my name
to get ruined.

383
00:23:16,967 --> 00:23:18,633
So what do you want me to do?

384
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:20,233
Forget everything?

385
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:23,833
Come on, let's catch some fish.

386
00:23:23,933 --> 00:23:26,267
Wow, Eden!

387
00:23:26,333 --> 00:23:30,567
Candidate number 2 is so ready
for the swimming competition.

388
00:23:30,633 --> 00:23:32,133
Judge,

389
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:35,333
what can you say
about her performance?
